This paper discusses the robustness of deep neural networks to adversarial perturbations, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the use of local intrinsic dimensionality (LID) to study adversarial subspaces, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE.
